    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><em><strong>Nov 2023</strong></em><br>\nHere is the comparison list of the most widely known methods</p>\n<div class=\"s-table-container\">\n<table class=\"s-table\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>fun</th>\n<th>accuracy</th>\n<th>return</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>System.nanoTime()</td>\n<td>Precise</td>\n<td><strong>High-resolution</strong><br>the current value of the running Java Virtual Machines time source, in nanoseconds.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>System.currentTimeMillis()</td>\n<td>High</td>\n<td><strong>Very efficient</strong><br>the difference, measured in milliseconds, between the current time and midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Calendar.getInstance().getTimeInMillis()</td>\n<td>High</td>\n<td><strong>Low efficiency</strong><br>the current time as UTC milliseconds from the epoch.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>new Date().getTime()</td>\n<td>High</td>\n<td><strong>Low efficiency</strong><br>the number of milliseconds since January 1, 1970, 00:00:00 GMT represented by this date.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Instant.now().getEpochSecond()</td>\n<td>Medium</td>\n<td><strong>Requires Api 26</strong><br>the seconds from the epoch of 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Clock.System.now()</td>\n<td>High</td>\n<td><strong>Kotlin</strong><br></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>"
  }, {
